article.description: — Keegan Records posted 16 points and eight rebounds as Colgate romped past Holy Cross 87-60 on Monday night.
article.headline: Records scores 16 to lift Colgate past Holy Cross 87-60
article.linkText: Records scores 16 to lift Colgate past Holy Cross 87-60
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- — Keegan Records posted 16 points and eight rebounds as Colgate romped past Holy Cross 87-60 on Monday night. Ryan Moffatt and Nelly Cummings each had 14 points for Colgate (12-11, 8-2 Patriot League), which won its fourth straight game. Jack Ferguson had 12 points. Colgate totaled 47 first-half points, a season high for the team. Kyrell Luc had 21 points for the Crusaders (6-16, 4-6). ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
